    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-09-26T16:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-09-26T16:40:00-05:00" n="335"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d335">
                <head>335. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Jordan</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d335fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 785.00/9–2458. Top Secret; Limited Distribution. Drafted by Parker
                        and <persName corresp="#p_RSW1">Rockwell</persName> and cleared by <persName
                            corresp="#p_BJL2">Berry</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1958-09-26T17:40:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 26, 1958—5:40 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>902. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 970.<note n="2" xml:id="d335fn2">
                        <ref target="#d329">Document 329</ref>.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>. Department shares Embassy view that Jordan
                    cannot for long maintain present stance toward Arab neighbors and that some form
                    of accommodation will take place. While we not seeking maintain <gloss
                        target="#t_HKJ1">HKJ</gloss> as western fortress in Middle East, any abrupt
                    or forceful change in Jordan’s status would be likely precipitate hostilities in
                    area. We are therefore concerned that political future <gloss target="#t_HKJ1"
                        >HKJ</gloss> be determined by agreement between parties concerned and that
                    any changes which occur should be brought about in orderly and peaceful
                    manner.</p>
                <p>Our attitude toward successor government would depend on its composition, policy
                    toward US and West and manner its coming to power. End <gloss target="#t_FYI1"
                        >FYI</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HCAJ1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Herter</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
